  • Constructor Details

    • ContentType

      public ContentType(String primaryType, String subType, List<Parameter> parameters)
      Constructor.
      Parameters:
      primaryType - the primary component of the media type, e.g. "text", "multipart", "image", or "application". May not be null
      subType - the subtype of the media type, e.g. "plain" for text/plain or "mixed" for multipart/mixed. May not be null
      parameters - optional list of parameters for the content type, in order. May be null
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if primaryType or subType are null

  • Method Details

    • getPrimaryType

      public String getPrimaryType()
      Returns the primary type for this content type, e.g. "text" or "image".
      Returns:
      the primary type (the part of the media type before the '/')

    • isPrimaryType

      public boolean isPrimaryType(String primaryType)
      Indicates whether this content type matches the specified primary type. Comparisons are case insensitive.
      Parameters:
      primaryType - the primary media type to test
      Returns:
      true if this content-type matches, false otherwise

    • getSubType

      public String getSubType()
      Returns the subtype for this content type, e.g. "plain" or "jpeg".
      Returns:
      the subtype (the part of the media type after the '/')

    • isSubType

      public boolean isSubType(String subType)
      Indicates whether this content type matches the specified subtype. Comparisons are case insensitive.
      Parameters:
      subType - the media subtype to test
      Returns:
      true if this content-type matches, false otherwise

    • isMimeType

      public boolean isMimeType(String primaryType, String subType)
      Indicates whether this content type matches the specified primary type and subtype. Comparisons are case insensitive.
      Parameters:
      primaryType - the primary type to test
      subType - the subtype to test
      Returns:
      true if this content-type matches both primary and subtype, false otherwise

    • isMimeType

      public boolean isMimeType(String mimeType)
      Indicates whether this content type matches the specified MIME type string. The string should be in "type/subtype" format. Comparisons are case insensitive.
      Parameters:
      mimeType - the MIME type to test (e.g., "text/html", "multipart/form-data")
      Returns:
      true if this content-type matches the given MIME type, false otherwise

    • getParameters

      public List<Parameter> getParameters()
      Returns the parameters for this content type, if any.
      Returns:
      the unmodifiable parameter list or null if there are no parameters

    • getParameter

      public String getParameter(String name)
      Returns the first value for the specified parameter name, if any. Parameter names are case insensitive.
      Parameters:
      name - the name of the parameter
      Returns:
      the value of the first parameter in this content-type that matches the given name, or null if there is no such parameter

    • toHeaderValue

      public String toHeaderValue()
      Serializes this content type to RFC 2045/2231 compliant header format. Parameter values containing non-ASCII characters will be encoded using RFC 2231 extended parameter syntax.
